1
00:00:03,253 --> 00:00:05,839
[theme music playing]

2
00:01:22,541 --> 00:01:28,463
EXECUTION

3
00:01:32,217 --> 00:01:35,929
[Rem] You will continue to kill criminals
whose names are broadcast.

4
00:01:36,138 --> 00:01:39,766
Outside of that, you're free
to use the Death Note however you wish.

5
00:01:39,933 --> 00:01:41,810
That's the only condition.

6
00:01:42,561 --> 00:01:45,355
If everything happens
as Light Yagami planned,

7
00:01:45,522 --> 00:01:47,274
this should help to save Misa.

8
00:01:48,150 --> 00:01:50,277
Do as I say, and you'll get what you want.

9
00:01:50,444 --> 00:01:52,904
In the end, it works out well
for both of us.

10
00:01:53,113 --> 00:01:56,533
I suppose, for someone in your position,
you'd call this good business.

11
00:02:02,289 --> 00:02:03,457
50 DAYS IN PRISON

12
00:02:03,540 --> 00:02:05,667
[L] Mr. Yagami, are you all right?

13
00:02:06,126 --> 00:02:08,712
There's no reason for you
to keep doing this to yourself.

14
00:02:09,504 --> 00:02:13,050
[Yagami] It's been over a month since Kira
started killing criminals again.

15
00:02:13,425 --> 00:02:14,968
And as far as I'm concerned,

16
00:02:15,093 --> 00:02:18,764
that's all the proof I need
to be sure that my son isn't Kira.

17
00:02:19,049 --> 00:02:22,549
So, then all that's left
is for you to be sure.

18
00:02:23,268 --> 00:02:24,686
One way or another,

19
00:02:24,811 --> 00:02:27,064
when I get out of here
it will be with my son.

20
00:02:28,857 --> 00:02:30,901
Wow. The Chief can be pretty stubborn.

21
00:02:32,069 --> 00:02:33,737
Light, how are you feeling right now?

22
00:02:34,738 --> 00:02:36,573
Uh. I'm okay.

23
00:02:36,865 --> 00:02:37,824
Ryuzaki,

24
00:02:38,075 --> 00:02:40,160
I know that in the time
I've been in prison

25
00:02:40,285 --> 00:02:41,912
no new criminals have died,

26
00:02:42,371 --> 00:02:45,332
however, that suggests to me
that Kira must be someone

27
00:02:45,457 --> 00:02:47,709
who is intimately familiar
with my situation.

28
00:02:47,834 --> 00:02:49,044
-And if that's the case--
-No, Light.

29
00:02:49,127 --> 00:02:52,381
The reason criminals have stopped dying
is because you are Kira.

30
00:02:52,589 --> 00:02:54,216
No! I'm not Kira.

31
00:02:54,383 --> 00:02:56,385
How many times do I have to say it?

32
00:02:57,052 --> 00:02:59,513
[L] If Light were Kira,
he'd know that I was bluffing.

33
00:02:59,638 --> 00:03:01,098
So, why is he getting so upset?

34
00:03:01,473 --> 00:03:02,849
He honestly seems clueless.

35
00:03:03,892 --> 00:03:05,268
This is just cruel.

36
00:03:05,477 --> 00:03:06,978
I don't care if he is a suspect.

37
00:03:07,062 --> 00:03:09,773
Light still has a right to know
that criminals are being killed again.

38
00:03:11,274 --> 00:03:13,652
-[L in distorted voice] Amane.
-[Misa] Yes?

39
00:03:13,777 --> 00:03:14,945
[L] Are you okay?

40
00:03:15,195 --> 00:03:16,238
You seem tired.

41
00:03:16,488 --> 00:03:18,073
[Misa] Is that supposed to be funny?

42
00:03:18,615 --> 00:03:20,325
How are you expecting me to look

43
00:03:20,492 --> 00:03:23,120
after being tied up and questioned
for this many days?

44
00:03:23,203 --> 00:03:24,246
[L] Hm, that's true.

45
00:03:25,080 --> 00:03:26,873
Please, just let me go.

46
00:03:27,374 --> 00:03:28,834
I want to see Light.

47
00:03:29,209 --> 00:03:30,085
Please.

48
00:03:30,752 --> 00:03:31,837
Light...

49
00:03:32,178 --> 00:03:33,263
back me.

50
00:03:35,090 --> 00:03:38,427
Uh... I'm not sure how much more of this
the three of them can take.

51
00:03:38,552 --> 00:03:41,805
Ryuzaki, you have no reason
to keep Light locked up anymore.

52
00:03:41,888 --> 00:03:44,850
Do the right thing and let him go.
Then we can get the Chief out too.

53
00:03:45,308 --> 00:03:46,852
Criminals are still being killed,

54
00:03:46,977 --> 00:03:49,771
even though Misa and Light haven't had
access to any of that information.

55
00:03:50,021 --> 00:03:52,315
We know that much already.
So, what are you waiting for?

56
00:03:52,649 --> 00:03:53,859
Not true.

57
00:03:53,942 --> 00:03:55,861
All we really know at this point
is that Amane

58
00:03:55,944 --> 00:03:58,530
harbors an unnaturally strong
devotion for Light Yagami.

59
00:03:59,781 --> 00:04:00,907
Ryuzaki.

60
00:04:01,116 --> 00:04:03,660
I'm sorry, but with all due respect,
from where I'm standing,

61
00:04:03,744 --> 00:04:05,662
it's starting to look like
you're only doing this

62
00:04:05,746 --> 00:04:08,248
because you don't want to admit
that you were wrong about Light.

63
00:04:08,331 --> 00:04:10,083
Yes, I figured you'd say that.

64
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:11,585
Okay, fine.

65
00:04:11,752 --> 00:04:14,212
But we do know
that Kira killed Lind L. Tailor

66
00:04:14,296 --> 00:04:15,756
and those FBI agents, right?

67
00:04:15,881 --> 00:04:17,799
As Light, said, if Kira could kill

68
00:04:17,924 --> 00:04:20,427
while under surveillance
and without access to information,

69
00:04:20,594 --> 00:04:22,095
there would've been no need.

70
00:04:22,220 --> 00:04:23,680
If they didn't pose a threat to him,

71
00:04:23,847 --> 00:04:25,640
then why would he bother killing them?

72
00:04:25,766 --> 00:04:27,267
Kira doesn't kill without good reason.

73
00:04:27,350 --> 00:04:29,269
I've heard you say so yourself
on more than one occasion.

74
00:04:29,352 --> 00:04:30,729
Oh, I see.

75
00:04:30,896 --> 00:04:33,190
If he was able to kill
under these circumstances,

76
00:04:33,273 --> 00:04:35,525
then he wouldn't have been
concerned about those FBI agents

77
00:04:35,609 --> 00:04:36,818
in the first place.

78
00:04:37,986 --> 00:04:39,446
[Aizawa] It's already been 50 days.

79
00:04:39,529 --> 00:04:41,323
There's no point to this anymore.

80
00:04:42,282 --> 00:04:45,786
Ryuzaki, it's time
to start looking for the real Kira.

81
00:05:02,719 --> 00:05:04,304
Yes, I understand.

82
00:05:06,264 --> 00:05:07,641
[L] Mr. Yagami.

83
00:05:07,808 --> 00:05:09,100
Yes. What is it?

84
00:05:09,309 --> 00:05:12,312
Would you be willing
to come to headquarters just once?

85
00:05:12,479 --> 00:05:15,857
I'd like to discuss my thoughts with you
but it must be done in person.

86
00:05:16,066 --> 00:05:19,569
However, above all else,
I need to talk to you as Light's father.

87
00:05:21,238 --> 00:05:22,864
All right. I'll come.

88
00:05:23,549 --> 00:05:24,912
[dramatic music playing]

89
00:05:25,242 --> 00:05:27,619
[inaudible dialogue]

90
00:05:40,674 --> 00:05:44,553
THREE DAYS LATER

91
00:05:45,345 --> 00:05:46,888
Honestly, all this time

92
00:05:47,055 --> 00:05:49,307
I never pictured you
as an old man, Mr. Stalker.

93
00:05:49,474 --> 00:05:50,684
I'm not your stalker.

94
00:05:50,767 --> 00:05:53,270
-I'm a detective with the NPA.
-What?

95
00:05:53,520 --> 00:05:55,105
Wait. I remember now!

96
00:05:55,313 --> 00:05:58,400
You told me I was being arrested
for being the Second Kira.

97
00:05:58,525 --> 00:06:00,068
You mean, that was for real?

98
00:06:01,444 --> 00:06:02,571
No, you're a stalker.

99
00:06:02,654 --> 00:06:04,906
There's no way the police
would blindfold me and tie me up

100
00:06:04,990 --> 00:06:06,449
all fetishy like that.

101
00:06:06,658 --> 00:06:09,786
Anyways, it's kind of weird that you have
my hands and feet all tied up,

102
00:06:09,911 --> 00:06:11,538
even though you're planning to let me go.

103
00:06:11,872 --> 00:06:13,456
Please, just keep quiet.

104
00:06:25,468 --> 00:06:26,928
-Light!
-[Light] Misa?

105
00:06:27,095 --> 00:06:29,055
Oh, I've missed you so much, Light.

106
00:06:29,180 --> 00:06:30,765
Dad, tell me, what's all this about?

107
00:06:31,016 --> 00:06:32,059
He's your dad?

108
00:06:32,392 --> 00:06:34,352
Oh, my God.
I totally called your dad a stalker,

109
00:06:34,436 --> 00:06:36,521
and said he was old
and all kinds of other rude stuff.

110
00:06:36,813 --> 00:06:39,691
Pleased to meet you. My name's Misa Amane.
I'm Light's girlfriend...

111
00:06:39,816 --> 00:06:40,942
They're all yours, Chief.

112
00:06:44,613 --> 00:06:46,781
Let's go. Get in the car.

113
00:06:51,995 --> 00:06:54,122
I was starting to think
I'd never get out of there.

114
00:06:54,205 --> 00:06:56,207
But it feels good to finally be cleared.

115
00:06:56,374 --> 00:06:57,375
[Yagami] No.

116
00:06:57,709 --> 00:06:59,836
I'm afraid you two are being taken...

117
00:07:00,253 --> 00:07:01,630
to your execution.

118
00:07:03,423 --> 00:07:06,426
I wanted to be the one
to escort you to the execution site.

119
00:07:06,509 --> 00:07:08,595
It was secretly built
in an underground facility,

120
00:07:08,678 --> 00:07:09,638
not far from here.

121
00:07:09,888 --> 00:07:11,056
-Execution?
-What?

122
00:07:11,139 --> 00:07:13,350
-Is this a joke?
-What the hell are you talking about?

123
00:07:13,433 --> 00:07:15,435
[Yagami] L is convinced
that you are Kira, Light,

124
00:07:15,644 --> 00:07:18,063
and that Misa Amane is the Second Kira.

125
00:07:18,188 --> 00:07:21,107
He is convinced that the only way
we can prevent the murders,

126
00:07:21,191 --> 00:07:22,567
is to execute the two of you.

127
00:07:23,318 --> 00:07:25,528
I don't understand.
The killings have already stopped.

128
00:07:25,737 --> 00:07:27,530
[Yagami] No, they never stopped.

129
00:07:27,614 --> 00:07:28,740
They never...

130
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:31,117
That's not what he told me.
So, he was lying?

131
00:07:31,326 --> 00:07:33,995
L was trying to get
a confession out of you, Light.

132
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:35,372
He would have said anything.

133
00:07:35,664 --> 00:07:37,415
But at this point that's not the problem.

134
00:07:38,291 --> 00:07:39,417
It's political now.

135
00:07:39,542 --> 00:07:43,213
You see, L's suggestion that the killings
would stop if you two were eliminated,

136
00:07:43,296 --> 00:07:44,798
was unanimously accepted

137
00:07:44,923 --> 00:07:47,592
by top officials in the UN
and the Japanese government.

138
00:07:48,343 --> 00:07:50,011
They want Kira to disappear.

139
00:07:50,178 --> 00:07:51,596
No trial, no publicity.

140
00:07:51,972 --> 00:07:53,556
But that's completely insane!

141
00:07:53,640 --> 00:07:55,058
Please, Dad. I'm not Kira!

142
00:07:55,141 --> 00:07:57,394
He's right. What kind of a father
are you anyway?

143
00:07:57,477 --> 00:07:59,104
This is your own son
you're talking about!

144
00:07:59,187 --> 00:08:01,022
L made this decision, not me.

145
00:08:01,272 --> 00:08:03,274
And his word is absolute.

146
00:08:03,525 --> 00:08:06,152
Over the years,
he's tackled the most difficult cases,

147
00:08:06,236 --> 00:08:07,445
solving all of them.

148
00:08:07,570 --> 00:08:09,072
He's never been wrong.

149
00:08:09,406 --> 00:08:10,657
You trust L

150
00:08:10,949 --> 00:08:13,159
more than you trust me, your own son?

151
00:08:13,535 --> 00:08:16,454
L went so far as to stake his life
on this theory.

152
00:08:16,621 --> 00:08:19,541
If the killings don't stop,
then he too will be executed.

153
00:08:19,874 --> 00:08:20,875
Huh?

154
00:08:21,126 --> 00:08:22,252
L said that?

155
00:08:22,377 --> 00:08:23,628
What could he be thinking?

156
00:08:23,753 --> 00:08:25,880
I know that given the material evidence

157
00:08:25,964 --> 00:08:28,258
this might seem
like the only logical solution.

158
00:08:28,633 --> 00:08:30,552
But... he is making a mistake!

159
00:08:30,844 --> 00:08:32,637
How could L come to this conclusion?

160
00:08:32,971 --> 00:08:34,806
-[heartbeat]
-Something's is not right here.

161
00:08:34,889 --> 00:08:35,849
It's just...

162
00:08:35,974 --> 00:08:37,559
It's not like L at all.

163
00:08:37,684 --> 00:08:40,228
The L I know
would rely on hard evidence.

164
00:08:40,395 --> 00:08:41,980
He has to have the truth.

165
00:08:42,147 --> 00:08:44,315
Is he really trying to end it like this?

166
00:08:44,441 --> 00:08:46,276
All right. We're almost there.

167
00:08:49,070 --> 00:08:50,321
[tires screeching]

168
00:08:51,573 --> 00:08:52,574
[Light and Misa groan]

169
00:08:55,076 --> 00:08:56,286
[cawing]

170
00:09:03,793 --> 00:09:05,170
Where are we right now?

171
00:09:05,503 --> 00:09:07,589
Why did you bring us out
to the middle of nowhere?

172
00:09:07,672 --> 00:09:09,424
-What is this?
-Wait a sec!

173
00:09:09,591 --> 00:09:11,718
I bet he brought us out here to let us go.

174
00:09:12,093 --> 00:09:13,094
This will do.

175
00:09:13,178 --> 00:09:15,764
Looks like there's nobody around
to see us out here.

176
00:09:15,889 --> 00:09:18,558
I decided it would be better for us
if I brought you here,

177
00:09:18,641 --> 00:09:20,101
instead of the execution site.

178
00:09:21,644 --> 00:09:22,896
Listen to me.

179
00:09:24,731 --> 00:09:27,317
I'm going to kill you here
and then kill myself.

180
00:09:27,442 --> 00:09:28,318
[gasping]

181
00:09:28,401 --> 00:09:30,278
What? What are you talking about, Dad?

182
00:09:30,445 --> 00:09:32,530
-You can't! That's crazy!
-How can you say that!

183
00:09:32,655 --> 00:09:34,324
You'd kill your only son for L?

184
00:09:34,407 --> 00:09:36,659
If you want to die so bad
why don't you kill yourself?

185
00:09:36,743 --> 00:09:38,495
If you do this,
you're no different than Kira.

186
00:09:38,828 --> 00:09:40,497
I'm nothing like Kira.

187
00:09:40,830 --> 00:09:45,210
I'm bound by my responsibilities
as a parent and as chief of the NPA.

188
00:09:45,585 --> 00:09:47,921
Dad, come on. She's right!

189
00:09:48,088 --> 00:09:50,965
Think about it. If we die here,
the truth will never be revealed!

190
00:09:51,091 --> 00:09:53,593
-Please, Dad. You have to let us escape!
-[Yagami] It's too late.

191
00:09:54,219 --> 00:09:56,054
Either way, you'll be executed.

192
00:09:56,471 --> 00:09:59,641
At least with this,
I'll be the one to do it.

193
00:10:00,266 --> 00:10:01,643
[pants, whimpers]

194
00:10:01,851 --> 00:10:03,561
Please, stop, Dad! I'm not Kira!

195
00:10:04,187 --> 00:10:07,482
If I die here, Kira wins!
Can't you see?

196
00:10:08,566 --> 00:10:11,152
Amane, I'm going to die here with my son.

197
00:10:11,277 --> 00:10:12,862
But I have no reason to kill you.

198
00:10:12,987 --> 00:10:14,322
Do you understand what I'm saying?

199
00:10:15,073 --> 00:10:17,867
It's only a matter of time
before the police locate this car.

200
00:10:18,118 --> 00:10:20,161
Then they'll transport you
to the original site

201
00:10:20,328 --> 00:10:21,496
and execute you there.

202
00:10:22,997 --> 00:10:24,207
[whimpers]

203
00:10:24,791 --> 00:10:26,167
Light, my son...

204
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:30,630
from one murderer to another,
I'll see you in Hell.

205
00:10:31,172 --> 00:10:32,298
No, Dad!

206
00:10:35,468 --> 00:10:37,262
No! Stop it!

207
00:10:37,470 --> 00:10:39,514
[gunshot]

208
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,535
Light, my son...

209
00:11:00,702 --> 00:11:03,371
from one murderer to another,
I'll see you in Hell.

210
00:11:03,496 --> 00:11:04,706
No, Dad!

211
00:11:04,831 --> 00:11:05,707
[gunshot]

212
00:11:05,915 --> 00:11:06,916
[birds cawing]

213
00:11:18,761 --> 00:11:22,348
[Light and Misa panting]

214
00:11:24,184 --> 00:11:25,852
You... used a blank?

215
00:11:28,897 --> 00:11:30,940
[sighs] Thank goodness.

216
00:11:31,733 --> 00:11:33,067
"Thank goodness"?

217
00:11:33,234 --> 00:11:35,153
What's going on? I don't understand.

218
00:11:35,320 --> 00:11:37,197
Please, forgive me, you two.

219
00:11:37,488 --> 00:11:39,032
I know that was hard on you.

220
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:41,868
But it was the only way
I could get you out of prison.

221
00:11:42,410 --> 00:11:43,828
-You must understand.
-Oh.

222
00:11:44,037 --> 00:11:47,874
I only agreed to do this because
I believe in your innocence, Light.

223
00:11:48,541 --> 00:11:50,084
Were you watching, Ryuzaki?

224
00:11:50,501 --> 00:11:51,836
I did exactly as you said,

225
00:11:51,920 --> 00:11:54,422
and as you can see, I'm still alive.

226
00:11:55,548 --> 00:11:57,926
[L] Yes, it was
a convincing performance.

227
00:11:58,718 --> 00:12:00,845
If Amane were the Second Kira,

228
00:12:00,929 --> 00:12:03,306
who only needs to see a person's face
to kill them,

229
00:12:03,556 --> 00:12:05,141
there is no doubt
she would have killed you

230
00:12:05,225 --> 00:12:07,143
before you had the chance
to fire your weapon.

231
00:12:07,685 --> 00:12:10,146
Also, if Light was in fact Kira,

232
00:12:10,355 --> 00:12:11,898
the Kira I know wouldn't hesitate

233
00:12:11,981 --> 00:12:14,150
to kill even his own father
to save himself.

234
00:12:14,609 --> 00:12:17,028
With Light in particular,
I cannot rule out the possibility

235
00:12:17,111 --> 00:12:19,739
that he may have seen
through our act at some point.

236
00:12:20,073 --> 00:12:23,534
However, as we agreed,
I will end their confinement immediately.

237
00:12:24,244 --> 00:12:25,453
And as we discussed,

238
00:12:25,578 --> 00:12:27,455
Amane will remain under surveillance

239
00:12:27,580 --> 00:12:29,207
until Kira is apprehended.

240
00:12:29,749 --> 00:12:33,628
Although she insists the tapes we found
were just occult videos,

241
00:12:33,795 --> 00:12:35,964
the physical evidence we have,
plus her confession,

242
00:12:36,130 --> 00:12:37,257
suggest otherwise.

243
00:12:37,340 --> 00:12:39,759
Hey! No fair! You still suspect me?

244
00:12:40,051 --> 00:12:41,844
If I were you, I wouldn't complain.

245
00:12:42,011 --> 00:12:44,013
You get to go back to your normal life.

246
00:12:44,097 --> 00:12:46,849
If you're innocent, the surveillance
shouldn't be a threat to you.

247
00:12:46,975 --> 00:12:49,143
Think of it as a complimentary
police protection.

248
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:50,770
Oh, I get it.

249
00:12:51,187 --> 00:12:52,730
Since I'm not the Second Kira,

250
00:12:52,814 --> 00:12:55,525
it'll be kind of like having
my very own private bodyguards.

251
00:12:56,109 --> 00:12:58,319
[L] As for your part
in this agreement, Light...

252
00:12:58,945 --> 00:13:01,406
you and I will be together 24/7.

253
00:13:01,948 --> 00:13:05,493
And that's how we'll remain
until we've brought Kira to justice.

254
00:13:12,250 --> 00:13:13,418
Fine by me.

255
00:13:13,501 --> 00:13:14,752
We will catch Kira.

256
00:13:15,211 --> 00:13:16,254
Together.

257
00:13:16,671 --> 00:13:19,215
[L] Yes. I look forward
to working with you.

258
00:13:23,678 --> 00:13:25,930
[Light] Are you sure
this is necessary, Ryuzaki?

259
00:13:26,347 --> 00:13:28,933
This is as difficult for me
as it is for you.

260
00:13:29,267 --> 00:13:32,937
So, is this what you meant by being
together 24 hours a day with him?

261
00:13:33,062 --> 00:13:34,772
Looking at you,
I never would have guessed.

262
00:13:34,939 --> 00:13:37,191
Are you on that side of the fence,
Ryuzaki?

263
00:13:37,275 --> 00:13:40,028
I told you I'm not doing this
because I want to. Okay?

264
00:13:40,236 --> 00:13:41,487
But Light belongs to me.

265
00:13:41,571 --> 00:13:42,989
I don’t wanna share him with you.

266
00:13:43,114 --> 00:13:44,699
If you're with him 24/7,

267
00:13:44,782 --> 00:13:46,576
then how are we supposed
to go on dates together?

268
00:13:46,701 --> 00:13:49,662
Oh, you can still go on dates.
But it will have to be the three of us.

269
00:13:49,746 --> 00:13:53,249
No way! Are you telling me
we have to kiss in front of you and stuff?

270
00:13:53,333 --> 00:13:55,001
I'm not telling you to do anything.

271
00:13:55,084 --> 00:13:56,878
But, yes, I suppose I would be watching.

272
00:13:57,003 --> 00:13:58,838
-[Misa] That's so gross!
-[Yagami growls quietly]

273
00:13:58,921 --> 00:14:00,423
[Misa] You really are a pervert,
aren't you?

274
00:14:00,506 --> 00:14:02,759
[L] Light, please,
make Misa stop talking now.

275
00:14:03,134 --> 00:14:05,136
Listen, Misa, that's enough.

276
00:14:05,553 --> 00:14:08,431
The police have already established
that it was you who sent those tapes.

277
00:14:08,556 --> 00:14:10,350
So, you're lucky
to even be here right now.

278
00:14:10,475 --> 00:14:12,268
They have every right
to keep you in prison.

279
00:14:12,352 --> 00:14:13,936
How can you even say that, Light?

280
00:14:14,062 --> 00:14:15,813
In case you forgot, I'm your girlfriend.

281
00:14:15,980 --> 00:14:17,774
Don't you trust you own soulmate?

282
00:14:17,982 --> 00:14:19,650
Uh... What do you mean, "soulmate"?

283
00:14:19,817 --> 00:14:23,112
You're the one who said you fell in love
with me at first sight, Misa.

284
00:14:23,488 --> 00:14:25,907
So, why did you kiss me
if you didn't have feelings for me?

285
00:14:26,032 --> 00:14:27,700
You took advantage of me!

286
00:14:28,242 --> 00:14:30,828
[squealing] Stupid! Stupid! Stupid!

287
00:14:31,454 --> 00:14:33,623
About this love at first sight.

288
00:14:33,748 --> 00:14:36,709
It happened in Aoyama on May 22,
didn't it?

289
00:14:37,168 --> 00:14:38,336
So what?

290
00:14:38,419 --> 00:14:40,380
Why did you choose that day
to go to Aoyama?

291
00:14:40,505 --> 00:14:42,673
And do you remember what you wore?

292
00:14:42,799 --> 00:14:43,800
It's like I told you.

293
00:14:43,925 --> 00:14:45,968
I just happened to go there.
I don't know why.

294
00:14:46,052 --> 00:14:49,597
I don't remember how I felt
and I don't even know what I was wearing.

295
00:14:49,764 --> 00:14:53,351
Anyway, since when do I need a reason
to hang out in Aoyama, huh?

296
00:14:53,684 --> 00:14:56,187
And somehow
when you came back from Aoyama,

297
00:14:56,270 --> 00:14:57,855
you knew that you were in love
with some guy

298
00:14:57,939 --> 00:14:59,357
-and that his name was Light.
-Yes.

299
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:02,276
And yet, you yourself have no idea
how you came to know his name.

300
00:15:02,402 --> 00:15:03,736
Yeah. So what?

301
00:15:03,903 --> 00:15:05,947
Tell me, what if Light was Kira?

302
00:15:06,030 --> 00:15:07,698
-How would it make you feel?
-Huh?

303
00:15:07,782 --> 00:15:09,659
How would I feel
if Light was Kira?

304
00:15:09,826 --> 00:15:10,910
That's right.

305
00:15:13,287 --> 00:15:14,705
That would be wonderful!

306
00:15:14,914 --> 00:15:16,874
I mean, I've always been grateful to Kira

307
00:15:16,999 --> 00:15:18,835
for punishing the man
who murdered my parents.

308
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:20,962
So, if I found out that Light
was actually Kira,

309
00:15:21,045 --> 00:15:22,547
that would be like a bonus for me.

310
00:15:22,672 --> 00:15:24,674
If anything, it would make me
love him even more.

311
00:15:24,757 --> 00:15:26,426
Even though it's, like,
practically impossible

312
00:15:26,509 --> 00:15:28,052
to love him more than I already do!

313
00:15:28,177 --> 00:15:30,388
It's Kira, though.
You'd love him even more for that?

314
00:15:30,471 --> 00:15:32,932
I mean, wouldn't you be afraid?
What if he tried to kill you?

315
00:15:33,182 --> 00:15:35,435
You're talking about Light being Kira?

316
00:15:35,518 --> 00:15:37,103
He wouldn't be scary at all.

317
00:15:37,228 --> 00:15:38,688
I'm a supporter of Kira,

318
00:15:38,771 --> 00:15:40,940
so if I found out
my Light was actually him,

319
00:15:41,107 --> 00:15:43,067
I'd think of how I could be helpful.

320
00:15:43,234 --> 00:15:44,569
[quiet growling]

321
00:15:44,735 --> 00:15:46,279
[L] That's very generous of you,

322
00:15:46,404 --> 00:15:48,698
but I am pretty sure
Kira doesn't need your help.

323
00:15:49,365 --> 00:15:51,534
Well, Misa, based on
what you've just told me,

324
00:15:51,659 --> 00:15:54,203
there can be no mistake
that you are the Second Kira.

325
00:15:54,704 --> 00:15:57,874
But you've made it so painfully obvious,
that I don't really wanna believe it.

326
00:15:58,082 --> 00:16:01,544
Whatever. It's not believable
because I'm not the Second Kira. Okay?

327
00:16:02,462 --> 00:16:05,423
Anyway, for the time being,
you'll remain under surveillance.

328
00:16:05,506 --> 00:16:07,091
When you do go out, if needed,

329
00:16:07,216 --> 00:16:09,635
you'll be able to contact us
using this room's extension.

330
00:16:09,719 --> 00:16:11,679
For the most part,
your life will return to normal.

331
00:16:11,804 --> 00:16:14,682
But from now on, for all private
and work-related affairs,

332
00:16:14,849 --> 00:16:17,143
Mr. Matsuda will be accompanying you
as your new manager,

333
00:16:17,226 --> 00:16:18,269
-Matsui...
-Matsui here.

334
00:16:18,352 --> 00:16:21,314
[L] Your agency's been paid to
keep quiet and the police don't know.

335
00:16:21,439 --> 00:16:22,523
Don't blow his cover.

336
00:16:22,607 --> 00:16:24,025
This old guy is my manager?

337
00:16:24,192 --> 00:16:25,568
Oh! You can't be serious.

338
00:16:25,776 --> 00:16:27,236
Come on, what's wrong with me, Misa-Misa?

339
00:16:27,361 --> 00:16:28,654
-Is it the tie? Cause I can--
-[growls]

340
00:16:31,699 --> 00:16:35,369
Would you cut it out with all this dating,
kissing and Misa-Misa talk already?

341
00:16:35,620 --> 00:16:37,079
This is the Kira investigation!

342
00:16:37,288 --> 00:16:38,748
Stop messing around!

343
00:16:39,123 --> 00:16:40,625
Sorry about that, Aizawa.

344
00:16:41,292 --> 00:16:42,668
No, it's all right.

345
00:16:42,752 --> 00:16:45,213
I just figured out what the problem is.

346
00:16:46,005 --> 00:16:49,217
Misa Amane, it's time for you
to go to your room.

347
00:16:49,425 --> 00:16:50,384
[Misa] Why?

348
00:16:50,468 --> 00:16:52,512
-Out you go!
-Don't--

349
00:16:52,595 --> 00:16:55,473
Hey, Light! Let's go on a date,
even if it is the three of us!

350
00:16:56,265 --> 00:16:57,850
[growls]

351
00:16:57,975 --> 00:17:00,269
So, Light, are you serious about her?

352
00:17:00,394 --> 00:17:03,564
No way. Like I told you earlier,
it's completely one-sided.

353
00:17:03,648 --> 00:17:05,942
Then could you at least
pretend to be serious,

354
00:17:06,025 --> 00:17:07,443
for the sake of the investigation?

355
00:17:07,527 --> 00:17:09,737
There are two things
I know about Amane for sure.

356
00:17:09,820 --> 00:17:11,364
One, that she is involved in this.

357
00:17:11,864 --> 00:17:12,823
And two...

358
00:17:12,990 --> 00:17:14,617
that she is in love with you.

359
00:17:15,326 --> 00:17:17,328
You-- You want me
to become intimate with her

360
00:17:17,453 --> 00:17:19,664
to gather information
about the Second Kira?

361
00:17:19,747 --> 00:17:22,583
Yes. I think you could do it
without arousing her suspicions.

362
00:17:22,667 --> 00:17:25,795
And Amane would definitely be
a valuable source of information for us.

363
00:17:25,920 --> 00:17:29,590
Not to mention, this is the main reason
why I agreed to release the two of you.

364
00:17:30,591 --> 00:17:31,634
Ryuzaki.

365
00:17:33,052 --> 00:17:34,554
As much as I wanna help you,

366
00:17:34,720 --> 00:17:36,430
and as important as
the Kira case is to me,

367
00:17:36,514 --> 00:17:38,849
I can't manipulate a woman's feelings
like that.

368
00:17:39,392 --> 00:17:40,685
Hmm...

369
00:17:41,227 --> 00:17:42,770
[Light] Please, try to understand,

370
00:17:42,979 --> 00:17:45,773
to me, exploiting another
person's feelings for personal gain

371
00:17:45,898 --> 00:17:47,108
is unforgivable,

372
00:17:47,233 --> 00:17:49,485
and I won't allow myself
to stoop that low.

373
00:17:49,860 --> 00:17:51,696
[L] There's something wrong
with this picture.

374
00:17:52,029 --> 00:17:54,657
It's as if he is a different person now.

375
00:17:54,991 --> 00:17:56,951
Is it possible this is an act?

376
00:17:57,702 --> 00:17:58,953
If this is genuine,

377
00:17:59,120 --> 00:18:02,582
it not only implies
that Amane was being controlled by Kira,

378
00:18:02,832 --> 00:18:04,458
but Light Yagami too.

379
00:18:04,542 --> 00:18:05,418
Huh?

380
00:18:05,626 --> 00:18:06,794
What's wrong, Ryuzaki?

381
00:18:06,961 --> 00:18:09,505
[L] N-- Nothing.
I suppose you're right, after all.

382
00:18:09,714 --> 00:18:13,175
However, considering Misa will have
a lot of contact with the public,

383
00:18:13,301 --> 00:18:16,470
it would be helpful if you could
make sure she doesn't leak information.

384
00:18:16,804 --> 00:18:17,763
By the way,

385
00:18:17,930 --> 00:18:20,057
do you think we could come up
with some kind of alternative

386
00:18:20,141 --> 00:18:23,311
to this system of moving
from hotel to hotel every few days?

387
00:18:23,561 --> 00:18:26,606
[L] Yes. In fact, I had
that very same thought some time ago.

388
00:18:26,689 --> 00:18:27,607
And so...

389
00:18:27,732 --> 00:18:30,318
I arranged for a facility to be built.

390
00:18:30,443 --> 00:18:34,405
Construction started right after my first
meeting with Mr. Yagami and the others.

391
00:18:34,614 --> 00:18:37,074
It should be finished in a few days.

392
00:18:37,742 --> 00:18:39,785
-Mm. Where is it... Here it is.
-[gasps]

393
00:18:40,870 --> 00:18:44,040
[L] Twenty-three floors above ground
and two below.

394
00:18:44,248 --> 00:18:46,375
Although it’s impossible
to see it from the outside,

395
00:18:46,542 --> 00:18:48,669
there are two helicopters
hidden on the roof.

396
00:18:48,753 --> 00:18:50,838
[Light] What? That's amazing.

397
00:18:51,672 --> 00:18:54,675
[L] Ideally, I want all of us
to spend as much time here as possible,

398
00:18:55,009 --> 00:18:58,095
If the investigation team grows,
we can accommodate up to 60 people.

399
00:18:58,596 --> 00:19:00,431
Misa shouldn't have any complaints,

400
00:19:00,556 --> 00:19:02,391
since she will have her own floor.

401
00:19:03,643 --> 00:19:05,227
This is truly impressive.

402
00:19:05,478 --> 00:19:07,355
-To go to such lengths...
-Hold on a second.

403
00:19:07,605 --> 00:19:10,107
Where did you find the finances
to build this thing?

404
00:19:10,983 --> 00:19:12,193
As you can see,

405
00:19:12,360 --> 00:19:14,987
it is my intention to solve this case,
no matter what it takes.

406
00:19:15,154 --> 00:19:16,364
That's how it is.

407
00:19:16,822 --> 00:19:18,616
I'm sorry, but how is that an answer.

408
00:19:18,699 --> 00:19:19,867
[Light] No, he's right.

409
00:19:20,159 --> 00:19:22,370
The mass killings are bad enough already.

410
00:19:22,495 --> 00:19:26,415
But personally, I will never forgive Kira
for putting my dad and I through this.

411
00:19:27,124 --> 00:19:29,543
I wanna solve this,
no matter what it takes.

412
00:19:29,752 --> 00:19:31,045
If you're serious about that,

413
00:19:31,128 --> 00:19:33,714
you should try to get close to Misa
and find about the Second--

414
00:19:33,798 --> 00:19:36,133
I can't. That goes against my principles.

415
00:19:36,258 --> 00:19:37,635
Right. You said that.

416
00:19:38,010 --> 00:19:39,804
-What a shame.
-[Aizawa chuckles]

417
00:19:39,929 --> 00:19:40,846
[Yagami] Huh?

418
00:19:40,971 --> 00:19:44,100
Um... nothing. I'm just feeling
really motivated right now, Chief.

419
00:19:44,475 --> 00:19:46,727
Ryuzaki, Chief Yagami, Light.

420
00:19:47,019 --> 00:19:49,105
Let's get out of here
and bring Kira to justice.

421
00:19:49,230 --> 00:19:50,314
[Yagami] Hmm.

422
00:19:50,439 --> 00:19:53,359
Excuse me, I couldn't help
but notice you missed my name.

423
00:20:03,911 --> 00:20:06,205
[man] Well, this looks like all of us.

424
00:20:06,831 --> 00:20:08,082
Let's get started, shall we?

425
00:20:08,833 --> 00:20:11,669
We're all here to further the growth
of the Yotsuba group.

426
00:20:11,836 --> 00:20:13,671
by reducing competition.

427
00:20:14,004 --> 00:20:15,131
So, the question is...

428
00:20:15,464 --> 00:20:16,924
who is going to die?

429
00:20:18,217 --> 00:20:21,011
I'm not thrilled that we
have to do this every single week.

430
00:20:21,220 --> 00:20:22,430
This may be irrelevant,

431
00:20:22,513 --> 00:20:25,558
but I have to wonder what prompted Kira
to start killing business people

432
00:20:25,683 --> 00:20:27,727
in addition to the usual criminals
and such?

433
00:20:27,852 --> 00:20:30,438
Come on now, haven't you figured
this out yet, Takahashi?

434
00:20:30,521 --> 00:20:31,397
Hm?

435
00:20:32,565 --> 00:20:35,443
This is the most advantageous
course of action for Kira.

436
00:20:35,943 --> 00:20:37,153
Advantageous?

437
00:20:37,361 --> 00:20:39,822
He's basically started
a killing service, Higuchi.

438
00:20:40,239 --> 00:20:42,950
You have a lot to say
considering how stupid you are.

439
00:20:43,200 --> 00:20:45,703
I'd hate to see you get killed
because of it.

440
00:20:46,620 --> 00:20:49,206
Despite the fact
that we are all relatively young,

441
00:20:49,498 --> 00:20:53,002
all of us are now frontrunners
to become Yotsuba's next CEO.

442
00:20:53,294 --> 00:20:56,547
Not to mention,
our salaries have virtually eclipsed

443
00:20:56,630 --> 00:20:59,008
those of the others
employees in the company.

444
00:21:00,301 --> 00:21:03,429
It's unlikely he would choose
to back a particular company.

445
00:21:03,804 --> 00:21:05,598
No matter how you look at it,

446
00:21:05,931 --> 00:21:07,391
one of the people in this room

447
00:21:07,641 --> 00:21:08,893
has to be Kira.

448
00:21:10,561 --> 00:21:14,690
TAKESHI OOI - EIICHI TAKAHASHI
MASAHIKO KIDA - KYOSUKE HIGUCHI

449
00:21:14,774 --> 00:21:16,299
So, back to business.

450
00:21:16,434 --> 00:21:17,852
Does anyone have a proposal?

451
00:21:18,611 --> 00:21:21,697
Who should we have Kira
eliminate this week, gentlemen?

452
00:21:23,741 --> 00:21:25,785
Humans beings are truly...

453
00:21:26,702 --> 00:21:28,913
disgusting creatures.

454
00:21:29,538 --> 00:21:36,406
TO BE CONTINUED
